snippet: Even if the court strikes down the individual mandate, many uninsured people are still likely to receive health coverage.
abstract: News analysis; the political ramifications of the Supreme Court's ruling on the Affordable Care Act will be big, regardless of whether the justices uphold the law or not, but experts say the practical effects will probably be less earth-shattering than people assume.
lead_paragraph: Even if the court strikes down the individual mandate, many uninsured people are still likely to receive health coverage.
